author: somi somi
text: As the IPCC report released.. and the US moves out from the Paris agreement... the main pressure is on China and India to move away from high emission based fossil fuel based economy... to achieve 1.5-degree Celsius but present commitment is not much tight.. sci and technology permit ur to cut the emission but there is a big gap b/w science and politics.. developed countries are not much serious... we need 45% emission removal.. to achieve the target... drought in north india.. flood in kerala.. heat wave in Europe forest fire in California so on and so forth it is difficult to retrieve the situation.. in world over in different form env. is reminding us to save humanity ... The US and China two biggest emitter.. around 45% of carbon emissions..and China further want to increase the emission. and the US removed out.. Canada moved out of Kyoto protocol... Russia Japan Germany missed their targets.... we are facing the alarming situation. Kyoto protocol over and Kyoto protocol two is not ratified... it indicates the Kyoto model is failed... in Paris agreement option is given to the new regime... evolve their own method to decrease carbon emission.. flexibility is given acc to the social situation of their county by problem sharing phenomena...  \n\nfor India specific... we have to highlight the scientific temper to create awareness among people for adopting cleaner energy... govt should installed a mechanism to promote cleaner energy with implementation... Govt must also promote on climate research in India centric... as we are doing some good in the solar alliance... but we have to change the mindset for our future prosperity and sustainable development... our policy needs to be aligned in multiple disciplinary ways to dictate climate change..
